package shiftmanager;

import javax.swing.*;
import java.awt.*;
import java.awt.event.*;

public class LoginForm extends JFrame {

    JTextField emailField;
    JPasswordField passField;
    JButton loginBtn;

    public LoginForm() {

        setSize(400, 400);
        setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.EXIT_ON_CLOSE);
        setLocationRelativeTo(null);
        setLayout(null);

        // ====================

        // ====================

        // ====================

        Image img = icon.getImage().getScaledInstance(150, 150, Image.SCALE_SMOOTH);
        JLabel imageLabel = new JLabel(new ImageIcon(img));
        // Center horizontally
        imageLabel.setBounds((400 - 150) / 2, 20, 150, 150);
        add(imageLabel);

        // ====================
        // Email field
        // ====================
        JLabel emailLabel = new JLabel("Email:");
        emailLabel.setBounds(50, 200, 80, 25);
        emailLabel.setForeground(Color.WHITE);
        add(emailLabel);

        emailField = new JTextField();
        emailField.setBounds(130, 200, 200, 25);
        add(emailField);

        // ====================
        // Password field

        JLabel passLabel = new JLabel("Password:");
        passLabel.setBounds(50, 240, 80, 25);
        passLabel.setForeground(Color.WHITE);
        add(passLabel);

        passField = new JPasswordField();
        passField.setBounds(130, 240, 200, 25);
        add(passField);

        // ====================
        // Login button
        // ====================
        loginBtn = new JButton("Login");
        loginBtn.setBounds(150, 290, 100, 30);
        add(loginBtn);

        // ====================
        // Login action
        // ====================
        loginBtn.addActionListener(new ActionListener() {
            public void actionPerformed(ActionEvent e) {
                String email = emailField.getText();
                String password = new String(passField.getPassword());

                // Simple hard-coded login check
                if (email.equals("admin@example.com") && password.equals("admin123")) {
                    JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "Login Successful!");
                } else {
                    JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, "Invalid Credentials", "Error", JOptionPane.ERROR_MESSAGE);
                }
            }
        });
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        });

Ah! Now I understand clearly you want the entire login panel (image + email + password + button) centered in the JFrame, not just the image. The easiest and cleanest way is to use a JPanel with a GridBagLayout (or BoxLayout) so that all components stay together and are centered.

java
package shiftmanager;

import javax.swing.*;
import java.awt.*;
import java.awt.event.*;

public class LoginForm extends JFrame {

    JTextField emailField;
    JPasswordField passField;
    JButton loginBtn;

    public LoginForm() {
        setTitle("Shift Manager Login");
        setSize(500, 500);
        setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.EXIT_ON_CLOSE);
        setLocationRelativeTo(null); // center the frame on screen

        // ====================
        // Background color
        // ====================
        getContentPane().setBackground(new Color(148, 0, 211));
        getContentPane().setLayout(new GridBagLayout()); // center the panel

        // ====================
        // Center panel
        // ====================
        JPanel panel = new JPanel();
        panel.setBackground(new Color(148, 0, 211)); // same violet
        panel.setLayout(new GridBagLayout());
        GridBagConstraints gbc = new GridBagConstraints();
        gbc.insets = new Insets(10, 10, 10, 10);
        gbc.fill = GridBagConstraints.HORIZONTAL;

        // ====================
        // Login image
        // ====================
        ImageIcon icon = new ImageIcon(getClass().getResource("/icons/login.png"));
        Image img = icon.getImage().getScaledInstance(150, 150, Image.SCALE_SMOOTH);
        JLabel imageLabel = new JLabel(new ImageIcon(img));
        gbc.gridx = 0;
        gbc.gridy = 0;
        gbc.gridwidth = 2;
        gbc.anchor = GridBagConstraints.CENTER;
        panel.add(imageLabel, gbc);

        // ====================
        // Email label and field
        // ====================
        gbc.gridwidth = 1;
        gbc.anchor = GridBagConstraints.LINE_END;
        gbc.gridy = 1;
        gbc.gridx = 0;
        JLabel emailLabel = new JLabel("Email:");
        emailLabel.setForeground(Color.WHITE);
        panel.add(emailLabel, gbc);

        gbc.anchor = GridBagConstraints.LINE_START;
        gbc.gridx = 1;
        emailField = new JTextField(15);
        panel.add(emailField, gbc);

        // ====================
        // Password label and field
        // ====================
        gbc.anchor = GridBagConstraints.LINE_END;
        gbc.gridy = 2;
        gbc.gridx = 0;
        JLabel passLabel = new JLabel("Password:");
        passLabel.setForeground(Color.WHITE);
        panel.add(passLabel, gbc);

        gbc.anchor = GridBagConstraints.LINE_START;
        gbc.gridx = 1;
        passField = new JPasswordField(15);
        panel.add(passField, gbc);

        // ====================
        // Login button
        // ====================
        gbc.gridy = 3;
        gbc.gridx = 0;
        gbc.gridwidth = 2;
        gbc.anchor = GridBagConstraints.CENTER;
        loginBtn = new JButton("Login");
        panel.add(loginBtn, gbc);

        // ====================
        // Add panel to frame
        // ====================
        add(panel);

        // ====================
        // Login action
        // ====================
        loginBtn.addActionListener(e -> {
            String email = emailField.getText();
            String password = new String(passField.getPassword());

            if (email.equals("admin@example.com") && password.equals("admin123")) {
                JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(this, "Login Successful!");
            } else {
                JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(this, "Invalid Credentials", "Error", JOptionPane.ERROR_MESSAGE);
            }
        });
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SwingUtilities.invokeLater(() -> {
            new LoginForm().setVisible(true);
        });
    }
}

package shiftmanager;

import javax.swing.*;
import java.awt.*;

public class AddShiftForm extends JFrame {

    private JTextField empField, dateField, startField, endField;
    private JButton addBtn, cancelBtn;

    public AddShiftForm() {
        setTitle("Add New Shift");
        setSize(500, 450);
        setLocationRelativeTo(null);
        setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.DISPOSE_ON_CLOSE);

        // Set violet background
        getContentPane().setBackground(new Color(148, 0, 211));
        getContentPane().setLayout(new GridBagLayout()); // center panel

        // Panel to hold form
        JPanel panel = new JPanel();
        panel.setBackground(new Color(148, 0, 211));
        panel.setLayout(new GridBagLayout());
        GridBagConstraints gbc = new GridBagConstraints();
        gbc.insets = new Insets(15, 10, 15, 10);
        gbc.fill = GridBagConstraints.HORIZONTAL;

        // Title
        JLabel lblTitle = new JLabel("Add Shift");
        lblTitle.setFont(new Font("Arial", Font.BOLD, 24));
        lblTitle.setForeground(Color.WHITE);
        gbc.gridx = 0;
        gbc.gridy = 0;
        gbc.gridwidth = 2;
        gbc.anchor = GridBagConstraints.CENTER;
        panel.add(lblTitle, gbc);

        // Employee
        gbc.gridwidth = 1;
        gbc.anchor = GridBagConstraints.LINE_END;
        gbc.gridy = 1;
        gbc.gridx = 0;
        JLabel l1 = new JLabel("Employee:");
        l1.setFont(new Font("Arial", Font.BOLD, 16));
        l1.setForeground(Color.WHITE);
        panel.add(l1, gbc);

        gbc.anchor = GridBagConstraints.LINE_START;
        gbc.gridx = 1;
        empField = new JTextField(20);
        empField.setFont(new Font("Arial", Font.PLAIN, 16));
        panel.add(empField, gbc);

        // Date
        gbc.anchor = GridBagConstraints.LINE_END;
        gbc.gridy = 2;
        gbc.gridx = 0;
        JLabel l2 = new JLabel("Date (YYYY-MM-DD):");
        l2.setFont(new Font("Arial", Font.BOLD, 16));
        l2.setForeground(Color.WHITE);

        gbc.anchor = GridBagConstraints.LINE_START;
        gbc.gridx = 1;
        dateField = new JTextField(20);
        dateField.setFont(new Font("Arial", Font.PLAIN, 16));
        panel.add(dateField, gbc);

        // Start Time
        gbc.anchor = GridBagConstraints.LINE_END;
        gbc.gridy = 3;
        gbc.gridx = 0;
        JLabel l3 = new JLabel("Start Time (HH:MM):");
        l3.setFont(new Font("Arial", Font.BOLD, 16));
        l3.setForeground(Color.WHITE);
        panel.add(l3, gbc);

        gbc.anchor = GridBagConstraints.LINE_START;
        gbc.gridx = 1;
        startField = new JTextField(20);
        startField.setFont(new Font("Arial", Font.PLAIN, 16));
        panel.add(startField, gbc);

        // End Time
        gbc.anchor = GridBagConstraints.LINE_END;
        gbc.gridy = 4;
        gbc.gridx = 0;
        JLabel l4 = new JLabel("End Time (HH:MM):");

        panel.add(endField, gbc);

        // Buttons
        gbc.gridy = 5;
        gbc.gridx = 0;

        JPanel btnPanel = new JPanel();

        addBtn = new JButton("Add Shift");

        cancelBtn.setPreferredSize(new Dimension(150, 40));
        btnPanel.add(cancelBtn);

        panel.add(btnPanel, gbc);

        add(panel);

        // Button actions
        addBtn.addActionListener(e -> onAddShift());
        cancelBtn.addActionListener(e -> dispose());
    }

    private void onAddShift() {
        String emp = empField.getText().trim();
        String date = dateField.getText().trim();
        String start = startField.getText().trim();
        String end = endField.getText().trim();

        if (emp.isEmpty() || date.isEmpty() || start.isEmpty() || end.isEmpty()) {
            JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(this, "Please fill all fields.", "Validation", JOptionPane.WARNING_MESSAGE);
            return;
        }

        ShiftDAO dao = new ShiftDAO();
        boolean ok = dao.addShift(emp, date, start, end);
        if (ok) {
            JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(this, "Shift added successfully.", "Success", JOptionPane.INFORMATION_MESSAGE);
            dispose();
        } else {
            JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(this, "Failed to add shift. Check console for errors.", "Error", JOptionPane.ERROR_MESSAGE);
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SwingUtilities.invokeLater(() -> new AddShiftForm().setVisible(true));
    }
}

java
package shiftmanager;

import java.util.*;
import java.sql.*;

public class ShiftDAO {

    public List<Shift> getAllShifts() {
        List<Shift> list = new ArrayList<>();

        try {
            Connection con = DBConnection.getConnection(); // Your DB connection class
            String sql = "SELECT empName, shiftDate, startTime, endTime FROM shifts"; // your table & columns
            PreparedStatement pst = con.prepareStatement(sql);
            ResultSet rs = pst.executeQuery();

            while (rs.next()) {
                String emp = rs.getString("empName");
                String date = rs.getString("shiftDate");
                String start = rs.getString("startTime");
                String end = rs.getString("endTime");

                list.add(new Shift(emp, date, start, end));
            }

            rs.close();
            pst.close();
            con.close();
        } catch (Exception e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }

        return list;
    }
}

1 CardPanel.java (Reusable rounded panel with shadow)

java
package shiftmanager;

import javax.swing.*;
import java.awt.*;

public class CardPanel extends JPanel {

    private int arcWidth = 30;  // roundness
    private int arcHeight = 30;
    private Color shadowColor = new Color(0, 0, 0, 100);
    private int shadowOffset = 5;

    public CardPanel() {
        setOpaque(false);
    }

    public CardPanel(int arcWidth, int arcHeight, Color shadowColor, int shadowOffset) {
        this.arcWidth = arcWidth;
        this.arcHeight = arcHeight;
        this.shadowColor = shadowColor;
        this.shadowOffset = shadowOffset;
        setOpaque(false);
    }

    @Override
    protected void paintComponent(Graphics g) {
        Graphics2D g2 = (Graphics2D) g.create();
        g2.setRenderingHint(RenderingHints.KEY_ANTIALIASING, RenderingHints.VALUE_ANTIALIAS_ON);

        // Draw shadow
        g2.setColor(shadowColor);
        g2.fillRoundRect(shadowOffset, shadowOffset, getWidth() - shadowOffset, getHeight() - shadowOffset, arcWidth, arcHeight);

        // Draw panel
        g2.setColor(getBackground());
        g2.fillRoundRect(0, 0, getWidth() - shadowOffset, getHeight() - shadowOffset, arcWidth, arcHeight);

        g2.dispose();
        super.paintComponent(g);
    }
}

// Add a new shift to the database
public boolean addShift(String emp, String date, String start, String end) {
    boolean success = false;
    try {
        Connection con = DBConnection.getConnection(); // Your DB connection
        String sql = "INSERT INTO shifts (empName, shiftDate, startTime, endTime) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?)";
        PreparedStatement pst = con.prepareStatement(sql);
        pst.setString(1, emp);
        pst.setString(2, date);
        pst.setString(3, start);

        int rows = pst.executeUpdate();
        success = rows > 0;

    }
    return success;
}

ShiftDAO.java (Complete)

java
package shiftmanager;

import java.sql.*;
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;

public class ShiftDAO {

    // Get all shifts from database
    public List<Shift> getAllShifts() {
        List<Shift> list = new ArrayList<>();
        try {
            Connection con = DBConnection.getConnection(); // your DB connection
            String sql = "SELECT empName, shiftDate, startTime, endTime FROM shifts";
            PreparedStatement pst = con.prepareStatement(sql);
            ResultSet rs = pst.executeQuery();

            while (rs.next()) {
                String emp = rs.getString("empName");
                String date = rs.getString("shiftDate");
                String start = rs.getString("startTime");
                String end = rs.getString("endTime");

                Shift shift = new Shift(emp, date, start, end);
                list.add(shift);
            }

            rs.close();
            pst.close();
            con.close();
        } catch (Exception e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }

        return list;
    }

    // Add a new shift to the database
    public boolean addShift(String emp, String date, String start, String end) {
        boolean success = false;
        try {
            Connection con = DBConnection.getConnection(); // your DB connection
            String sql = "INSERT INTO shifts (empName, shiftDate, startTime, endTime) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?)";
            PreparedStatement pst = con.prepareStatement(sql);
            pst.setString(1, emp);
            pst.setString(2, date);
            pst.setString(3, start);
            pst.setString(4, end);

            int rows = pst.executeUpdate();
            success = rows > 0;

            pst.close();
            con.close();
        } catch (Exception e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
        return success;
    }
}

Key Points:

  1. getAllShifts(): Returns a List<Shift> for the table in ViewShiftForm.

  2. addShift(): Inserts a new shift into the database for AddShiftForm.

  3. Make sure your database table shifts has these columns:

    • empName (VARCHAR)

    • shiftDate (DATE or VARCHAR)

    • startTime (VARCHAR or TIME)

    • endTime (VARCHAR or TIME)

  4. DBConnection.getConnection() should return a valid java.sql.Connection.

            PreparedStatement pst = con.prepareStatement(sql);
            ResultSet rs = pst.executeQuery();

            while (rs.next()) {
                String emp = rs.getString("empName");
                String date = rs.getString("shiftDate");
                String start = rs.getString("startTime");
                String end = rs.getString("endTime");
                list.add(new Shift(emp, date, start, end));
            }

            rs.close();
            pst.close();
            con.close();
        } catch (Exception e) { e.printStackTrace(); }
        return list;
    }

    public boolean addShift(String emp, String date, String start, String end) {
        boolean success = false;
        try {
            Connection con = DBConnection.getConnection();
            String sql = "INSERT INTO shifts (empName, shiftDate, startTime, endTime) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?)";
            PreparedStatement pst = con.prepareStatement(sql);
            pst.setString(1, emp);
            pst.setString(2, date);
            pst.setString(3, start);
            pst.setString(4, end);

            int rows = pst.executeUpdate();
            success = rows > 0;

            pst.close();
            con.close();
        } catch (Exception e) { e.printStackTrace(); }
        return success;
    }
}

1 CardPanel.java (Reusable card with rounded corners)

java
package shiftmanager;

import javax.swing.*;
import java.awt.*;

public class CardPanel extends JPanel {
    private int arcWidth = 30;
    private int arcHeight = 30;
    private Color shadowColor = new Color(0, 0, 0, 100);
    private int shadowOffset = 5;

    public CardPanel() { setOpaque(false); }

    @Override
    protected void paintComponent(Graphics g) {
        Graphics2D g2 = (Graphics2D) g.create();
        g2.setRenderingHint(RenderingHints.KEY_ANTIALIASING, RenderingHints.VALUE_ANTIALIAS_ON);
        // Draw shadow
        g2.setColor(shadowColor);
        g2.fillRoundRect(shadowOffset, shadowOffset, getWidth()-shadowOffset, getHeight()-shadowOffset, arcWidth, arcHeight);
        // Draw main panel
        g2.setColor(getBackground());
        g2.fillRoundRect(0,0,getWidth()-shadowOffset,getHeight()-shadowOffset,arcWidth,arcHeight);
        g2.dispose();
        super.paintComponent(g);
    }
}

package shiftmanager;

import java.sql.*;
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;

public class ShiftDAO {

    public List<Shift> getAllShifts() {
        List<Shift> list = new ArrayList<>();
        try {
            Connection con = DBConnection.getConnection();
            String sql = "SELECT empName, shiftDate, startTime, endTime FROM shifts";
            PreparedStatement pst = con.prepareStatement(sql);
            ResultSet rs = pst.executeQuery();

            while(rs.next()) {
                list.add(new Shift(
                    rs.getString("empName"),
                    rs.getString("shiftDate"),
                    rs.getString("startTime"),
                    rs.getString("endTime")
                ));
            }

            rs.close();
            pst.close();
            con.close();
        } catch(Exception e) { e.printStackTrace(); }
        return list;
    }

    public boolean addShift(String emp, String date, String start, String end) {
        boolean success = false;
        try {
            Connection con = DBConnection.getConnection();
            String sql = "INSERT INTO shifts (empName, shiftDate, startTime, endTime) VALUES (?,?,?,?)";
            PreparedStatement pst = con.prepareStatement(sql);
            pst.setString(1, emp);
            pst.setString(2, date);
            pst.setString(3, start);
            pst.setString(4, end);
            int rows = pst.executeUpdate();
            success = rows > 0;
            pst.close();
            con.close();
        } catch(Exception e) { e.printStackTrace(); }
        return success;
    }
}

Ah! That error is a classic NullPointerException when loading an icon.

The key part of the error:

csharp
Cannot invoke "java.net.URL.toExternalForm()" because "location" is null

It means Java cannot find the image file at the path you gave:

java
ImageIcon icon = new ImageIcon(getClass().getResource("/icons/dashboard.png"));

Why it happens

  1. The path /icons/dashboard.png is not found in your classpath.

  2. getResource() returns null, so new ImageIcon(null) fails.

Common causes:

  • The icons folder is not inside src.

  • The image name is misspelled (case-sensitive: Dashboard.png dashboard.png).

  • Leading / assumes root of classpath, so if its in src/shiftmanager/icons it must be /shiftmanager/icons/dashboard.png.

How to fix

Option 1: Place icons in src/icons (recommended)

  • Put all PNGs (dashboard.png, login.png, addshift.png, viewshift.png) directly inside src/icons/.

  • Then load like this:

java
ImageIcon icon = new ImageIcon(getClass().getResource("/icons/dashboard.png"));

Option 2: If icons are inside shiftmanager/icons/

  • Then path must be:

java
ImageIcon icon = new ImageIcon(getClass().getResource("/shiftmanager/icons/dashboard.png"));

Option 3: Test loading

Before using the image, test:

java
URL loc = getClass().getResource("/icons/dashboard.png");
System.out.println(loc); // should print a URL, not null

If it prints null, the path is wrong.

Option 4: Use absolute file path (not recommended for production)

java
ImageIcon icon = new ImageIcon("C:/Users/.../dashboard.png");

but better to fix classpath.

Summary

  • Make sure all icon files exist.

  • Make sure the resource path matches your folder structure exactly.

  • Check capitalization (Java is case-sensitive).

ShiftDAO.java

java
package shiftmanager;

import java.sql.*;
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;

public class ShiftDAO {

    // Get all shifts
    public List<Shift> getAllShifts() {
        List<Shift> list = new ArrayList<>();
        try {
            Connection con = DBConnection.getConnection();
            String sql = "SELECT empName, shiftDate, startTime, endTime FROM shifts";
            PreparedStatement pst = con.prepareStatement(sql);
            ResultSet rs = pst.executeQuery();

            while (rs.next()) {
                list.add(new Shift(
                        rs.getString("empName"),
                        rs.getString("shiftDate"),
                        rs.getString("startTime"),
                        rs.getString("endTime")
                ));
            }

            rs.close();
            pst.close();
            con.close();
        } catch (Exception e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
        return list;
    }

    // Add a new shift
    public boolean addShift(String emp, String date, String start, String end) {
        boolean success = false;
        try {
            Connection con = DBConnection.getConnection();
            String sql = "INSERT INTO shifts (empName, shiftDate, startTime, endTime) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?)";
            PreparedStatement pst = con.prepareStatement(sql);
            pst.setString(1, emp);
            pst.setString(2, date);
            pst.setString(3, start);
            pst.setString(4, end);

            int rows = pst.executeUpdate();
            success = rows > 0;

            pst.close();
            con.close();
        } catch (Exception e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
        return success;
    }

    // Get shifts for a specific employee
    public List<Shift> viewShifts(String empName) {
        List<Shift> list = new ArrayList<>();
        try {
            Connection con = DBConnection.getConnection();
            String sql = "SELECT empName, shiftDate, startTime, endTime FROM shifts WHERE empName=?";
            PreparedStatement pst = con.prepareStatement(sql);
            pst.setString(1, empName);
            ResultSet rs = pst.executeQuery();

            while (rs.next()) {
                list.add(new Shift(
                        rs.getString("empName"),
                        rs.getString("shiftDate"),
                        rs.getString("startTime"),
                        rs.getString("endTime")
                ));
            }

            rs.close();
            pst.close();
            con.close();
        } catch (Exception e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
        return list;
    }
}

  2. addShift() inserts a new shift into database.

  3. viewShifts(String empName) returns shifts filtered by employee name or email, used in ViewShiftForm.

  4. Database columns must match: empName, shiftDate, startTime, endTime.

  5. Uses DBConnection.getConnection() to connect to your MySQL database.

ChatGPT said:

Ah! That error happens because youre trying to use net.proteanit.sql.DbUtils, which is not included in standard Java.

The line:

java
table.setModel(net.proteanit.sql.DbUtils.resultSetToTableModel(rs));

will throw an error unless you have the rs2xml.jar library added to your project.

Options to fix

Option 1: Add rs2xml.jar

  1. Download it: https://sourceforge.net/projects/finalangelsanddemons/files/

  2. Add it to your projects Build Path (Eclipse: Right-click Build Path Add External JARs)

  3. Import in your code:

java
import net.proteanit.sql.DbUtils;

Then your line will work:

java
table.setModel(DbUtils.resultSetToTableModel(rs));

Option 2: Use DefaultTableModel manually

If you dont want to use external libraries, you can convert the ResultSet to a DefaultTableModel yourself:

java
import javax.swing.table.DefaultTableModel;
import java.sql.*;

public void populateTable(ResultSet rs, JTable table) throws SQLException {
    DefaultTableModel model = new DefaultTableModel();
    ResultSetMetaData rsmd = rs.getMetaData();
    int cols = rsmd.getColumnCount();

    // Add column names
    for(int i=1; i<=cols; i++){
        model.addColumn(rsmd.getColumnName(i));
    }

    // Add rows
    while(rs.next()){
        Object[] row = new Object[cols];
        for(int i=0; i<cols; i++){
            row[i] = rs.getObject(i+1);
        }
        model.addRow(row);
    }

    table.setModel(model);
}

Then replace:

java
table.setModel(DbUtils.resultSetToTableModel(rs));

with:

java
populateTable(rs, table);

Summary

  • net.proteanit.sql.DbUtils is from rs2xml.jar, not standard Java.

  • Either add the jar or use DefaultTableModel manually as above.

Ah! Now I understand youre asking in terms of web development terminology: you want all your UI (forms, tables, buttons) to appear in a single page, similar to a webpage.

In Java Swing, there isnt an actual HTML page, but you can achieve this using a single main container JFrame that holds multiple JPanels. The concept is:

How to structure it:

  1. Main container:

    • A JFrame acts as the main window like your webpage.

    • This will be your single page where everything is displayed.

  2. Sections (like web sections):

    • Each form (Login, AddShift, ViewShift) can be a JPanel.

    • You switch between panels using a CardLayout.

    • This is exactly like multiple pages in a single webpage.

Example: MainContainer.java

java
package shiftmanager;

import javax.swing.*;
import java.awt.*;

public class MainContainer extends JFrame {

    private JPanel mainPanel;
    private CardLayout cardLayout;

    public MainContainer() {
        setTitle("Shift Manager Webpage View");
        setSize(800, 600);
        setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.EXIT_ON_CLOSE);
        setLocationRelativeTo(null);

        cardLayout = new CardLayout();
        mainPanel = new JPanel(cardLayout);

        // Create panels
        LoginFormPanel loginPanel = new LoginFormPanel(this);
        DashboardPanel dashboardPanel = new DashboardPanel(this);
        AddShiftPanel addShiftPanel = new AddShiftPanel(this);
        ViewShiftPanel viewShiftPanel = new ViewShiftPanel(this);

        // Add panels to main container
        mainPanel.add(loginPanel, "login");
        mainPanel.add(dashboardPanel, "dashboard");
        mainPanel.add(addShiftPanel, "addshift");
        mainPanel.add(viewShiftPanel, "viewshift");

        add(mainPanel);
        showPanel("login"); // start with login panel
    }

    public void showPanel(String name) {
        cardLayout.show(mainPanel, name);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SwingUtilities.invokeLater(() -> new MainContainer().setVisible(true));
    }
}

How it works:

  1. MainContainer acts like a single webpage.

  2. CardLayout lets you switch between different forms/panels (Login, Dashboard, AddShift, ViewShift).

  3. Each form is now a JPanel instead of a separate JFrame.

  4. Switching is done via:

java
mainContainer.showPanel("dashboard");

  1. Everything is visible in one window, just like sections in a webpage.

So, in short:

  • The single page file is the main JFrame, here I named it MainContainer.java.

  • Inside it, all forms become JPanels, and switching is done via CardLayout.

        private void addShiftAction() {
            String emp = empField.getText().trim();
            String date = dateField.getText().trim();
            String start = startField.getText().trim();
            String end = endField.getText().trim();

            if(emp.isEmpty() || date.isEmpty() || start.isEmpty() || end.isEmpty()){
                JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(this, "Please fill all fields", "Warning", JOptionPane.WARNING_MESSAGE);
                return;
            }

            boolean ok = shiftDAO.addShift(emp, date, start, end);
            if(ok){
                JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(this, "Shift added successfully", "Success", JOptionPane.INFORMATION_MESSAGE);
                empField.setText(""); dateField.setText(""); startField.setText(""); endField.setText("");
            } else {
                JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(this, "Failed to add shift", "Error", JOptionPane.ERROR_MESSAGE);
            }
        }
    }

        private JScrollPane scroll;

        public ViewShiftPanel(MainContainer container) {
            setBackground(new Color(0,0,139));
            setLayout(new BorderLayout());

            JLabel title = new JLabel("View Shifts", SwingConstants.CENTER);
            title.setFont(new Font("Segoe UI", Font.BOLD, 22));
            title.setForeground(Color.WHITE);
            add(title, BorderLayout.NORTH);

            table = new JTable();
            scroll = new JScrollPane(table);
            add(scroll, BorderLayout.CENTER);
        }

        public void refreshTable() {
            List<Shift> shifts = shiftDAO.getAllShifts();
            String[] cols = {"Employee", "Date", "Start Time", "End Time"};
            DefaultTableModel model = new DefaultTableModel(cols,0);

            for(Shift s : shifts){
                model.addRow(new Object[]{s.getEmployee(), s.getDate(), s.getStartTime(), s.getEndTime()});
            }

            table.setModel(model);
        }
    }
